      <title>What a Crop?</title>
      <link>/post/covid-19-mx-deaths/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jun 2020 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>/post/covid-19-mx-deaths/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Crop selection is a multi-criteria decision. Depending on seasonality and type of irrigation, it will modify the indicators among regions such as yield, Profit and the Water Footprint.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The use of intensive indicators gives us an alternative to analyze the relationships and trade-offs between different flows. Likewise, it can provide better decision-making towards crops that have the highest nutritional benefit or a lower consumption of blue water.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;lsquo;Spatial Data Science is a Science of scale&amp;rsquo;&lt;/em&gt; The drill-down of the data highlights the differences of crop water footprint among sub-regions, irrigation methods and planting season.&lt;/p&gt;
